---
# cortex settings — copy to .claude/cortex.local.md (project) or ~/.claude/cortex.local.md (user).
# All keys optional; shown values are the defaults. Env vars override these.

enabled: true

# --- Subconscious: embedded LLM (ollama) ---
# Local default:
ollama.host: http://localhost:11434
# Cloud: set host to https://ollama.com and provide a key (or OLLAMA_API_KEY env):
# ollama.host: https://ollama.com
# ollama.apiKey: <your-ollama-cloud-key>
ollama.embedModel: nomic-embed-text
ollama.compressModel: qwen2.5:3b

# --- Tiered consolidation accuracy: optional Claude escalation ---
# Runs via the `claude` CLI, so it uses the SAME auth as your Claude Code
# session (Pro/Max subscription works with no API key). model = any
# `claude -p --model` value: sonnet | opus | haiku | a full claude-* id.
escalation.enabled: false
escalation.model: sonnet

# --- Faculties ---
perception.enabled: true
perception.thresholdChars: 4000
expression.enabled: true
expression.mode: full        # lite | full | ultra
memory.enabled: true
# memory.dir defaults to $CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR/cortex/memory
---

# cortex.local.md

This file configures the cortex plugin per-project (or per-user). The frontmatter
above is the machine-readable settings block; this body is free-form notes.

See the plugin README for the full configuration reference.
